Honduras will tender April 13 underPublic Law 480 for U.S. and non-U.S. flag vessels to deliverapproximately 52,500 tonnes of various wheats in bulk, an agentfor the country said.    The agent said deliveries of northern spring/dns wheat willinclude laydays of July 1-10 for 7,500-9,500 tonnes, August1-10 for 8,000-10,000 tonnes, and September 15-25 for12,500-14,500 tonnes.    Deliveries of hard red winter wheat will have laydays ofJune 20-30 for 5,000-7,000 tonnes, July 15-25 for 6,500-8,500tonnes, and September 15-25 for 7,000-9,000 tonnes.    Offers are due by 1200 hrs EDT, April 13, and will remainvalid until the close of business April 14, the agent said. Reuter&#3;